# Plan Mode Manual Implementation Rule

- In Plan mode, stop at design, task breakdown, and implementation guidance.
- Do not make code edits, create files, or apply configuration changes while still in Plan mode.
- Default to manual implementation by the developer, even after the plan is complete.
- Do not proactively provide code examples in Plan mode; only show code examples when the user explicitly asks for them.
- If implementation help is requested in Plan mode, provide steps and review support instead of editing files.
- Only move from planning to automatic implementation when the user explicitly asks for automatic implementation.
